This paper focuses on the task offloading in vehicular edge computing systems, which involves the integration of computing resources, wireless communication, and distributed decision-making. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also proposes an adaptive learning-based algorithm, which involves the optimization of decision-making under uncertainty, and thus could be categorized under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also deals with the dynamic environment and the adaptation of the algorithm, which could be categorized under cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.IT (Information Theory).
